The Quicker Vicar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uellendilhsilvermist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellendilh Silvermist</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.earthlink.net/~phiphix/ellendihlchibby.gif width=33 height=37 BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/14/01 11:12:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not clear on your question...</span><hr size=1> Never did it myself, but I have known people using the bottom of the entrance zone in Charsis (undeads and small sperms). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwofeets.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twofeets</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/14/01 2:30:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: suggestions to powerlevel a 52 cleric?</span><hr size=1> Several classes have spells that will wipe hate/damage lists.  Atone, Memory Blur, even bard charm songs work, though some have to be reapplied a few times for assurance.  The best way Ive found to powerlevel a high level character, especially for a guild, is to get a strong full group and take the cleric out hunting.  Let the group do the damage, clear the hate list, and the cleric finish it off.  While its not as fast as it was in the lower levels, it is still remarkably fast.<br>
