<br>
Your cleric just quad kited :) <p>Bllack Ader - Dr00d in Agony. Arf!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushweetiepah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>shweetie pah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/01 4:47:48 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: suggestions to powerlevel a 52 cleric?</span><hr size=1> I figured I'd post back here on what I did.<br>
<br>
Basically, between raiding 6 nights a week, I managed to level up my cleric very quickly by using basically what bllack ader said.  I don't exactly remember where I switched, but I did the whole thing in Cobalt Scar, starting on wyverns and moving to othmir warriors as the wyverns started to green out.<br>
<br>
The details:<br>
practice quad kiting on the subject and count the minimum number of nukes to kill group.  With Fist, I believe this was 4 on wyverns and 7 on othmir.  Quad kite groups to 1 less than that nuke, pull out AE root (finally a purpose to that spell!), move back a ways and begin camping.  Cleric has roots loaded and his job is now to allow druid to camp, which means rooting anything that breaks.  Once druid is at 5 seconds to camp, begin nuking.  As soon as druid is at char select screen, get back in and begin medding again.  Loot and med.  Rinse, repeat.<br>
<br>
Of course I was always just ahead of the over-camped nastiness curve.  As I was outgrowing wyverns, they began being overcamped.  When I started othmir I was practically guaranteed to be the only one hunting them.  Othmir began greening at 58, but were still good experience all the way up through 59.  At level 60 they have slowed down considerably, but I still pop in every now and then for buffer xp when I have a short bit of time available to grab a few xp.<br>
<br>
The loot wasn't bad.  When a level 60 paladin friend asked me to save him some crustacean armor (I thought he meant for a twink) and promptly put it on when I brought it to him it clued me in that maybe I shouldn't be selling the stuff to vendors, and I started transporting it to freeport.  I gave away about 1/3 of the drops I got to guildmates, friends, and random folks who popped in here and there to pull single othmir for the armor (thus fubaring my quad attempts) as bribes.  Anyway, between all the giveaways, rots, and me flooding the crustacean market I did pick up about 75k selling the drops I got during 58 and 59.<br>
<br>
Now the othmir are beginning to get camped.  There's not too many of them, so if you have to share spawns, the whole thing suddenly becomes less appealing.  There's ALMOST enough spawns for 2 quad kiters to coexist peacefully.<br>
<br>
XP rate was about as follows:<br>
52-53: 2blues an hour<br>
54-58: 1blue an hour<br>
59: 2hours per blue<br>
<br>
Anyway, doing this absolutely trashes your othmir faction on at least one character, so it is not for the faint of heart.  I looked at the big picture and made a weighted decision about how important getting my cleric to 60 as fast as possible was.  Once it became apparent that my guild needed me clericing more than it needed me druiding most of the time, it became worth some sacrifices and some hassles to get him there.<br>
<br>
for those critical of powerlevelling all the way to 60, I would say: keep in mind I did spend about 25-30 hours a week raiding with my cleric, so it's not like I never played him all the way up.  I just didn't do xp grinds in the typical locations.  <br>
<br>
Hope this info is of some use to someone, good luck levelling<br>
